subject: Track and Field
lead_paragraph: Christophe Lemaitre shrugged off damp and dismal conditions to win the 200 meters at the London Grand Prix, while the American world champion Carmelita Jeter was upset in the 100.
snippet: Christophe Lemaitre shrugged off damp and dismal conditions to win the 200 meters at the London Grand Prix, while the American world champion Carmelita Jeter was upset in the 100.
